Position: Sr. UI Developer

Location: Canada /Remote

Duration: 12+ Months

Job Description:
• Design and develop UI components based on functional specifications, requirements, market trends, and standards.
• Collaborate with all stakeholders to define the interaction architecture and behaviour of each platform to ensure that the user interface and customer journey is compelling for the end consumer on a visual, tactile and audible level.
• Optimizing performance and improving UI of existing components/application.
• Planning for common needs such as consistency, accessibility, and internationalization.
• Key contributor to the development of UI component library vision.
• Staying current on technologies and UI design trends/innovations and helping client/team in implementing the same.
• Communicates and collaborates with client, PO, and technical lead to develop and maintain aspects of responsiveness of application, including versions for various platforms.
• Help development team in easily adapt to responsive design and development process.
• Validate and iterate on your design solutions through feedback sessions, usability testing, and live testing on various devices.
• Own and deliver intuitive, efficient and delightful user experiences across the application.
• Follow ideas through from conception to execution and
• Identifies industry best practices for user experience and ensures that they are leveraged throughout organization to address business and user goals.
• Education and experience:
• Engineering degree or master’s degree in IT / Computer Science
• 10 years of experience in developing new responsive user-facing features from scratch.
• A minimum of 5 years’ experience as UI developer using react and or Redux technology
• Hands-on experience in development of responsive application with frameworks like bootstrap, material, W3.CSS, HTML5, and JavaScript technology
• Expertise in multiple front-end technologies such as Angular 12, Web Forms, Vue.JS, GitHub, Media Queries.
• Experience in creating modules, components, and packages for responsive applications.
• Familiar with software development lifecycles in addition to a variety of technical and analytical concepts with deep functional knowledge
• Solid experience in understanding of unit testing concepts and various responsive frameworks
• Experience in an Agile environment, effective communication & time management skills.
• Understanding of Design Patterns such as MVVM, Singleton, Dependency Injection, Command, Publish/Subscribe, Double-Checked locking, Event Based asynchronous.
• Understanding of Configuration Management and experience using TFS
• Good experience in leading UI front-end delivery with high fidelity to production front end code from a combination of wireframes, visual designs and design standards, solid understanding of UCD/HCI principles.

Job Types: Contract, Full-time

Pay: $45.72 - $65.00 per hour

Benefits:
• 401(k)
• Dental insurance
• Health insurance
• Paid time off

Our client is seeking a Lead. full-stack Java & React developer to build and support services to be shared by multiple teams and projects across the Department. The developer will lead small-to-medium projects or components of larger projects. Plan, analyze, design, and develop various micro-services in a cloud environment. The developer will also contribute to front-end React applications that consume those services as needed.

Specific Duties:

Under general direction, responsible for all phases of development and maintenance on assigned computer applications; communicates with business analysts to determine system requirements; researches system enhancements and problems; performs analysis and design of computer applications; performs programming and testing; performs related work as assigned. Position works directly with various levels of business and technical staff to determine sound technical solutions for business requirements. This position designs, codes, tests and documents micro-service applications and React front-end applications. Position has full technical knowledge of all phases of applications development and the development technologies utilized. Position provides production support for small and large, simple and complex applications including the ability to resolve problems in constrained timeframes. Position may have occasional off hours support. Position may be responsible for mentoring less experienced team members. Position may lead small-to-medium projects or components of larger projects.

Scope of Activities:
• Develop and debug application code
• Design java classes
• Conduct unit, integration, and customer acceptance testing
• Prepare code and application documentation
• Design and deploy micro-service databases in the Azure cloud, using relational or non-relational databases as appropriate
• Design and deploy React SPAs in the Azure cloud
• Consult with peers and subordinates on application issues
• Use application development tools and utilities as appropriate
• Assist and mentor peers and subordinates as appropriate
• Develop business problem definition
• Accomplish information collection, analysis and organization
• Prepare economic evaluation and estimates of time/effort required on projects
• Prepare solution development, recommendations and evaluation criteria

Required Experience:

At least 5 years Java development

At least 3 years developing micro-services, using Spring Boot or equivalent frameworks

At least 3 years writing and documenting REST APIs using the Open API (Swagger) specification.

At least 3 years HTML, CSS, and JavaScript experience

At least 3 years developing front-ends written in a modern SPA framework (Angular, React, Vue, etc.)

At least 3 years working with relational databases. Ability to write SQL queries and debug database related issues in Java applications.

Preferred Experience:

Familiarity with cloud application models (cloud native, serverless, etc.) strongly preferred.

Familiarity with application deployments in the Azure cloud preferred.

Familiarity with non-relational DBs is a plus (MongoDB, Cosmos DB, Dynamo DB, etc.)

Exposure to database automation frameworks (Liquibase, Flyway, etc.) is a plus.

Relevant certifications and training

Preferred to have a minimum of 3 years’ experience in all aspects of the software development lifecycle and workflow including, but not limited to:

Estimates

Target date planning

Work plan development and monitoring

Stakeholder communication

Quality Assurance

Development methods/techniques

Testing methods/techniques

Implementation planning and execution

Benefits: If you are basedin CA, GA

Health, Dental, Vision, 401K

As a React Developer, you will be responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining web applications using the React JavaScript library. You will collaborate with cross-functional teams to create responsive, high-performance user interfaces, ensuring an exceptional user experience.

Key Responsibilities:

Front-End Development: Create and maintain web applications by writing well-structured, efficient, and maintainable code in React.

User Interface Design: Collaborate with UI/UX designers to implement visually appealing and user-friendly interfaces.

Component Development: Build reusable and modular UI components that can be leveraged across the application.

State Management: Implement state management using tools like Redux or the React Context API to handle data and application state.

API Integration: Integrate with RESTful APIs or GraphQL to retrieve and update data from back-end services.

Performance Optimization: Identify and resolve performance bottlenecks for a smooth and responsive user experience.

Testing and Debugging: Conduct unit and integration tests and debug issues to maintain application quality.

Code Reviews: Participate in code reviews to ensure code quality and consistency.

Documentation: Create and maintain technical documentation for code, components, and systems.

Version Control: Utilize version control systems, such as Git, to manage and collaborate on code changes.

Qualifications:

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related field (or equivalent work experience).

Proven experience in front-end development with a strong focus on React.

Proficiency in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

Familiarity with state management libraries like Redux or Mobx.

Understanding of RESTful APIs and GraphQL.

Strong problem-solving and debugging skills.

Knowledge of responsive web design and cross-browser compatibility.

Experience with modern build tools and package managers (e.g., Webpack, Babel, npm).

Good communication and teamwork skills.

Benefits:

Competitive salary and performance-based bonuses.

Health, dental, and vision insurance.

Retirement savings plan (401k or similar).

Ongoing professional development and training opportunities.

Collaborative and innovative work environment.

If you're passionate about building intuitive and high-performing web applications using React and want to be part of a team that values innovation, we encourage you to apply for the React Developer position at [Your Company Name]. Help us shape the digital future with your expertise!

To apply, please submit your resume and a cover letter highlighting your relevant experience and explaining why you are interested in this role. We look forward to having you contribute to our success!

At CareContinuity we offer a platform that connects patients and providers in an exciting new way within the United States healthcare market. We have been doubling in size every year and are looking for enthusiastic team members with great communication and the ability to self-manage their workloads and ensure quality!

Since day one, we have employed a full time remote team. We develop great processes and teamwork that make working here easy and fun. We run an agile development process and our team members have great autonomy in how they execute their workloads.

In this role the frontend developer would be responsible for maintaining & developing new functionality for our platform hosted on Azure in the United States. This is a full-time position.

Our Stack:
• React
• Redux
• Slack/Teams
• Jira
• Git
